<h2 id=3D"id-8.1.7RASQL-Generalremarks">&nbsp;General remarks</h2>
<ul>
<li>&nbsp;In case of "only raise when event occurs at least x times", are w=
e going to fire every time the condition is true? Probably a bad idea becau=
se the user has no idea how often the event will occur as this depends on M=
FC settings.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"id-8.1.7RASQL-SubtledifferenceswithPQL(Peter'sQueryLanguage)">Sub=
tle differences with PQL (Peter's Query Language)</h2>
<ul>
<li>Multiple WHEN - THEN statements are possible</li>
<li>Calculation results can be named. These names can be used in WHEN THEN =
statements.&nbsp;</li>
<li>Boolean calculations are also possible in CALCULATE. Calculation result=
s can be used multiple times.&nbsp;</li>
<li>Provide a function CHANGED, which works similar to ROSE_ABOVE_THRESHOLD=
. It works as follows:
<ul>
<li style=3D"margin-left: 0.0px;">If no stored value is present, store a va=
lue and return TRUE</li>
<li style=3D"margin-left: 0.0px;">If the given value is different from the =
stored value, change the stored value and return TRUE</li>
<li style=3D"margin-left: 0.0px;">If the given value does not differ from t=
he stored value, return FALSE</li>
</ul></li>
<li style=3D"margin-left: 0.0px;">Provide a function TIMES_OCCURRED, which =
functions similarly to CHANGED. It works as follows:
<ul>
<li style=3D"margin-left: 0.0px;">Look in the database in a specific table =
how often this TIMES_OCCURRED wrote to it in the given period, and return t=
his value.&nbsp;</li>
<li style=3D"margin-left: 0.0px;">Just before returning, write a new record=
 to the table.&nbsp;</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-8.1.7RASQL-RemarksregardingRASQL">Remarks regarding RASQL</h2>
<ul>
<li>We need a better syntax for raw values =3D&gt; every(tp.SOC) ?&nbsp;</l=
i>
<li>How will EMAIL, WEBNOTIFICATION, etc work. Will we work with placeholde=
rs based on templates? =3D&gt; being investigated by PM</li>
<li>How do we refer to assets? By ID isn't ideal, perhaps we should allow b=
oth by name and by id. =3D&gt; both is allowed</li>
<li>How does the state storage in WHEN statements work? Every CHANGED, ROSE=
_ABOVE_THRESHOLD etc must have its own storage which cannot be mixed with o=
ther instances storage. Perhaps using named keys?&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
